{"id": "firmware-development--mobile-repeater-companion-repeat", "title": "Mobile repeater / companion repeat", "forum": "firmware-development", "messages": [{"id": "1448461081675694080", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:47 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:47 p.m.", "text": "I should probably separate these but they are also related. Mobile.repeater - Boolean knob added to repeater / companion node - default to off for repeaters Companion.repeat - Boolean knob to turn on and off repeat mode Mobile repeater when active uses <00> as its path node bytes on repeat. Any mobile repeater when seeeing a direct path message for 00 as next hop will repeat. Will act as a mini flood section in the path for any mobile repeaters that hear it Companion repeat enables repeat mode for companions by default mobile.repeat is true for companions Path will look like <ab> <cd> <00> <de> (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I should probably separate these but they are also related.  \n\nMobile.repeater - Boolean knob added to repeater / companion node - default to off for repeaters\n\nCompanion.repeat - Boolean knob to turn on and off repeat mode\n\nMobile repeater when active uses &lt;00&gt; as its path node bytes on repeat.  Any mobile repeater when seeeing a direct path message for 00 as next hop will repeat. Will act as a mini flood section in the path for any mobile repeaters that hear it \n\nCompanion repeat enables repeat mode for companions by default mobile.repeat is true for companions \n\nPath will look like &lt;ab&gt; &lt;cd&gt; &lt;00&gt; &lt;de&gt;</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Monday, December 15, 2025 2:31 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>7</span></div><div class=chatlog__reaction title=heart><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=❤️ src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/2764.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461661479632987", "author": "recrof", "author_handle": "recrof", "user_id": "205303085910720514", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/205303085910720514/8ccde84f87c6a23fe1212f4c9a64a4b8.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:49 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:49 p.m.", "text": "00 and FF are never naturally generated", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>00 and FF are never naturally generated</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461695700963338", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:49 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:49 p.m.", "text": "Shit", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Shit</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461866509664257", "author": "recrof", "author_handle": "recrof", "user_id": "205303085910720514", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/205303085910720514/8ccde84f87c6a23fe1212f4c9a64a4b8.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:50 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:50 p.m.", "text": "buf FF is reserved for broadcast", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>buf FF is reserved for broadcast</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461898994679848", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:50 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:50 p.m.", "text": "Can we use them in the path for hops like this ? I think it makes sense for mobile repeaters and companion repeaters", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Can we use them in the path for hops like this ?  I think it makes sense for mobile repeaters and companion repeaters</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461918208524451", "author": "recrof", "author_handle": "recrof", "user_id": "205303085910720514", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/205303085910720514/8ccde84f87c6a23fe1212f4c9a64a4b8.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:50 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:50 p.m.", "text": "00 might be better for this", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>00 might be better for this</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448461949158297862", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:50 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:50 p.m.", "text": "That’s fine", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>That’s fine</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448462217518252177", "author": "recrof", "author_handle": "recrof", "user_id": "205303085910720514", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/205303085910720514/8ccde84f87c6a23fe1212f4c9a64a4b8.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:51 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:51 p.m.", "text": "needs much more logic.. and I'm sure @Scott wanted to use scopes for repeating companions in wilderness", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>needs much more logic.. and I&#39;m sure <span class=\"chatlog__markdown-mention\" title=\"scott_33238\">@Scott</span>  wanted to use scopes for repeating companions in wilderness</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448462283243130920", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Wednesday, December 10, 2025 6:51 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-10 6:51 p.m.", "text": "And it allows them not to screw up dynamic learned paths since other such nodes could step in if needed", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>And it allows them not to screw up dynamic learned paths since other such nodes could step in if needed</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448585925620666410", "author": "ViezeVingertjes", "author_handle": "viezevingertjes", "user_id": "384752370795675660", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/384752370795675660/2fd6266a8fdbd7bc78af10dad7c6fd97.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, December 11, 2025 3:03 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-11 3:03 a.m.", "text": "My rogue nodes (repeaters) use ID 00, crypto lib didnt fit on them and just to lazy to set ID on build for each of them, it works though.", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>My rogue nodes (repeaters) use ID 00, crypto lib didnt fit on them and just to lazy to set ID on build for each of them, it works though.</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448593365842268202", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, December 11, 2025 3:32 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-11 3:32 a.m.", "text": "yeah thats expected", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>yeah thats expected</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/384752370795675660/2fd6266a8fdbd7bc78af10dad7c6fd97.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=viezevingertjes>ViezeVingertjes</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1448586206093774880')\"> Also made a companion repeat previously, but do note that they will always show up as &quot;Unknown&quot; in paths, as the app does not match the byte ID against other types than Repeater, and it has to be companion type to function normally as companion </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448597879987110010", "author": "ViezeVingertjes", "author_handle": "viezevingertjes", "user_id": "384752370795675660", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/384752370795675660/2fd6266a8fdbd7bc78af10dad7c6fd97.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, December 11, 2025 3:50 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-11 3:50 a.m.", "text": "Nodes advert with a type, it needs to advert as companion or you can't use it with the app as such, but that makes it unknown in paths", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Nodes advert with a type, it needs to advert as companion or you can&#39;t use it with the app as such, but that makes it unknown in paths</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1448598028385779766", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Thursday, December 11, 2025 3:51 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-11 3:51 a.m.", "text": "that isn't what i was suggesting the 00 path byte is only used as \"placeholder\"", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>that isn&#39;t what i was suggesting the 00 path byte is only used as &quot;placeholder&quot;</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1449060192200294595", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, December 12, 2025 10:27 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-12 10:27 a.m.", "text": "can think of this like in the MPLS world, the <00> as a MPLS multicast label", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>can think of this like in the MPLS world,  the &lt;00&gt; as a MPLS multicast label</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "<div class=chatlog__reactions><div class=chatlog__reaction title=thumbsup><img class=\"chatlog__emoji chatlog__emoji--small\" alt=👍 src=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f44d.svg loading=lazy> <span class=chatlog__reaction-count>1</span></div></div>", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1449980823519625360", "author": "n7jmv", "author_handle": "n7jmv", "user_id": "835630507344789555", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Sunday, December 14, 2025 11:26 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-14 11:26 p.m.", "text": "I think time bound client repeats for wilderness SAR work would be essential", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I think time bound client repeats for wilderness SAR work would be essential</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/205303085910720514/8ccde84f87c6a23fe1212f4c9a64a4b8.png?size=512\" alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=recrof>recrof</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1448462217518252177')\"> needs much more logic.. and I&#39;m sure <span class=\"chatlog__markdown-mention\" title=\"scott_33238\">@Scott</span>  wanted to use scopes for repeating companions in wilderness </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1450056931652800592", "author": "dz0ny", "author_handle": ".dz0ny", "user_id": "131465160257699840", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Monday, December 15, 2025 4:28 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-15 4:28 a.m.", "text": "Fyi https://github.com/dz0ny/MeshCore/tree/revert-ble-advert?tab=readme-ov-file#-recent-major-enhancements-revert-ble-advert-branch", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Fyi <a href=\"https://github.com/dz0ny/MeshCore/tree/revert-ble-advert?tab=readme-ov-file#-recent-major-enhancements-revert-ble-advert-branch\">https://github.com/dz0ny/MeshCore/tree/revert-ble-advert?tab=readme-ov-file#-recent-major-enhancements-revert-ble-advert-branch</a></span></div>", "embeds_html": ["<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=chatlog__embed-color-pill style=background-color:rgba(30,35,39,255)></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-content><div class=chatlog__embed-text><div class=chatlog__embed-title><a class=chatlog__embed-title-link href=\"https://github.com/dz0ny/MeshCore/tree/revert-ble-advert?tab=readme-ov-file\"><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">GitHub - dz0ny/MeshCore at revert-ble-advert</div></a></div><div class=chatlog__embed-description><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">A new lightweight, hybrid routing mesh protocol for packet radios - GitHub - dz0ny/MeshCore at revert-ble-advert</div></div></div><div class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-container><a class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail-link href=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/IFMVuaGHgzbm64Xrkpk1ttAHEyQcUDM-dcr2YeEeWG8/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/4a67eb03b27783675d1989726d2cb5babfd46ec08078df1714677ea755ea05e1/dz0ny/MeshCore> <img class=chatlog__embed-thumbnail src=https://images-ext-1.discordapp.net/external/IFMVuaGHgzbm64Xrkpk1ttAHEyQcUDM-dcr2YeEeWG8/https/opengraph.githubassets.com/4a67eb03b27783675d1989726d2cb5babfd46ec08078df1714677ea755ea05e1/dz0ny/MeshCore alt=Thumbnail loading=lazy data-canonical-url=https://opengraph.githubassets.com/4a67eb03b27783675d1989726d2cb5babfd46ec08078df1714677ea755ea05e1/dz0ny/MeshCore> </a></div></div></div></div>"], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1450132889088823306", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, December 15, 2025 9:30 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-15 9:30 a.m.", "text": "You implemented the 00 byte ?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>You implemented the 00 byte ?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "<div class=chatlog__reply><img class=chatlog__reply-avatar src=https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/2.png alt=Avatar loading=lazy><div class=chatlog__reply-author title=.dz0ny>dz0ny</div><div class=chatlog__reply-content><span class=chatlog__reply-link onclick=\"scrollToMessage(event,'1450057327137919109')\"> I implemented this and it was mix and match, you still need repeater somewhere. The difference is we have very difficult terrain, and even CB radios have problems, unless we put mobile repeater. One idea we are toying is to have attached repeater on a drone. Added benefit that drone can spot person/object, we message everyone hey there is a thing go check it out. Closest team sees the drone on map and goes to it. </span> <span class=chatlog__reply-edited-timestamp title=\"Monday, December 15, 2025 9:22 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1450163876141203630", "author": "Maveric", "author_handle": "mavericm1", "user_id": "232718149202608128", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/232718149202608128/836a891e888fecaebedf57a1b941dca3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, December 15, 2025 11